<article
  class="container-prose py-12 [&_h2]:mt-8 [&_h2]:text-xl [&_h3]:mt-5 [&_h3]:text-lg [&_h3]:font-semibold [&_li]:text-gray-400 [&_p]:mt-3 [&_p]:text-gray-400 [&_ul]:mt-3 [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:space-y-1 [&_ul]:pl-6"
>
  <LegalNotice />
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl">Code of Conduct</h1>
  <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
    Version 2.1+ (based on Contributor Covenant 2.1)
  </p>

  <h2>Our pledge</h2>
  <p>
    We pledge to make participation in the AI &amp; Vibe Coding Tour a
    harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size,
    visible or invisible disability, ethnicity, sex characteristics, gender
    identity and expression, level of experience, education, socio-economic
    status, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity
    and orientation.
  </p>

  <h2>Our standards</h2>
  <h3>Examples of positive behavior</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Demonstrating empathy and kindness toward other participants</li>
    <li>Being respectful of differing opinions, viewpoints, and experiences</li>
    <li>Giving and gracefully accepting constructive feedback</li>
    <li>
      Accepting responsibility and apologizing to those affected by mistakes
    </li>
    <li>Focusing on what is best for the community</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Examples of unacceptable behavior</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      The use of sexualized language or imagery, and unwelcome sexual attention
    </li>
    <li>Trolling, insulting comments, and personal or political attacks</li>
    <li>Public or private harassment</li>
    <li>Publishing others' private information without explicit permission</li>
    <li>
      Other conduct reasonably considered inappropriate in a professional
      setting
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Myanmar-context additions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Language:</strong> English is the instruction language. Burmese is welcome
      in support channels. We do not shame anyone for English fluency or accent.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Political content:</strong> We keep cohort channels and Tour-affiliated
      spaces free of political content (Myanmar political situation, international
      politics, party advocacy).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Religious and ethnic content:</strong> Likewise out of scope. Discussions
      about any specific religious or ethnic group as such are not welcome in cohort
      spaces.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Gender in tech:</strong> Zero tolerance for harassment of women in tech,
      including dismissive treatment of women's contributions, sexual comments, and
      gendered assumptions about competence.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Enforcement responsibilities</h2>
  <p>
    The lead instructor enforces this Code of Conduct. Reports of unacceptable
    behavior should be made privately to <a
      href="mailto:ai+conduct@vibecode.tours">ai+conduct@vibecode.tours</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>Enforcement guidelines</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>1. Correction</strong> — Private warning, with explanation of why.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>2. Warning</strong> — Continued or more serious violation. Time-out
      from specific channels. Apology required.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>3. Temporary ban</strong> — Serious violation. Removed from cohort for
      defined period (1-4 weeks).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>4. Permanent ban</strong> — Pattern of violations or single egregious
      violation. Removed from cohort permanently.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Attribution</h2>
  <p>
    This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1,
    available at <a
      href="https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/1/code_of_conduct.html"
      >contributor-covenant.org</a
    >.
  </p>
</article>
